The PMR-30 is a light weight, full size pistol chambered for the flat-shooting .22Magnum cartridge (.22WMR). The PMR-30 operates on a unique hybrid blowback/locked-breech system. title: For Sale:  S&W Smith & Wesson Model 39-2 Nickel RARE CLASSIC 9mm semi-auto DA/SA
postcontent:
Here is your chance to own a rare and collectible classic piece of American history! The model 39 was the first U.S. designed Double Action semi-automatic pistol marketed in the United States. The 39-2 is the improved second edition of this pistol design. Made from the 1970's to the early 1980's, this particular model was one of the last runs in either 1980 or 1981. Just looking at it though you would never guess this pistol is over 30 years old! The nickel finish is phenomenal! There are no real nicks or scratches on this gun, no pitting, no rust, no excessive wear, etc. There are some very minor surface scuffs visible in the photos which are to be expected from any reflective finish that has been handled and wiped down to clean. When polished up right this baby shines! 
It is apparent that the gun has a very low round count as the internals are barely worn and cleaner than most of my much newer guns. The gun has been upgraded with a VERY comfortable, ergonomic Pachmayr non-slip grip that fits the hand like a glove. One factory S&W 8rd magazine is included as well. The spring is still nice and tight, clean as a whistle. Some features are a magazine safety, external hammer, DA/SA trigger, manual decocker, and thumb safety. When the thumb lever is down, the gun is safe. If the hammer is back the lever can be pulled all the way down to safely decock the gun, physically blocking the hammer from the firing pin while lowering it.
Most important of all, she shoots like a dream! From the tight and smooth trigger squeeze to the minimal muzzle climb, the accuracy of this gun makes you feel like a pro putting rounds down range. I would never hesitate to arm myself with this 39-2 when in need.
These guns are seriously hard to come by in the nickel finish and without a doubt a valuable collectors' item. I would love to hang on to it myself just for sheer joy of owning this neat piece of history but I am a student paying for school who has a few too many toys. I need the money to pay for the fall semester.
I have seen these go on Gun Broker for $800+ so I feel like my asking price is fair for the condition of this gun. However, it is an asking price and I am open to other offers. Please don't hesitate to send them my way.
I do have more pictures available of different angles, the inside of the gun, etc. I am only allowed to upload 3 but you may contact me for more.

Larue PredatAR 5.56 Overview The PredatAR 5.56 is designed for those who are searching for a lightweight, ultra-reliable and accurate 5.56 mm NATO rifle for home-defense, competition-shooting or hunting. Even though we lightened certain features, there is still additional material in strategic areas to achieve maximum accuracy.

XTRAXN™ is a proprietary chamber feature added to reduce frictional forces caused by pressure-expanded cartridge cases bearing against chamber walls. title: For Sale:  NIB Saiga 12 Semi-auto Shotgun
postcontent:
The Saiga-12 IZSL- 433 is a 030-type semi-automatic shotgun based on the famous design of standard Saiga IZ-109. The shotgun is equipped with a magazine guide (magwell) and an automatic last round bolt hold open device in order to help facilitate easy reloads and insertion of the magazine. It also has a self regulating gas system, which allows greater flexibility in the type of ammo used. The top cover features a Picatinny rail on top allowing various optical devices to be attached to aid in target aquisition. The top cover is also hinged to the rear sight block in order to provide the top-mounted Picatinny rail with the ability to hold zero. An adjustable rear notched sight and front sight post are also standard on the shotgun to assist in accurate firing when no optical device is affixed.

 Saiga 12 shotguns were designed by the world-renown Russian engineer Mikhail Kalashnikov, who was the mastermind behind the creation of legendary AK-47. These shotguns are developed on the base of the Kalashnikov assault rifle and overenginnered for reliability. Made with a minimal amount of moving parts and simple operating procedures, the design succeeds in providing an easy to use, highly reliable shooting platform. The Saiga-12 is designed for high reliability in harsh environments. The magazines can be filled with a mixture of 2 ¾” and 3” shells allowing for a variety of ammunition to be used. This shotgun is designed for professional and sport hunting and small and medium-sized game under various climactic conditions. The removable magazine allows for quick reloads in situations when it’s required, like competitive shooting or a crisis situation. Saiga-12 is therefore great for tactical and home defense. All Saiga-12 shotguns have a threaded barrel so you can add various chokes or muzzle brakes.

title: For Sale:  Custom Heckler & Koch USP 45 Full-size Compensated
postcontent:
TRADES CONSIDERED.
This German made brute is an absolute BEAST! These highly sought after pistols have been a mainstay of the Special Operations community for years for the simple reason that HK works, and works well. This one is the prefered variant #1, meaning that the slide lever acts as a de-cocker and a safety. You can carry this "cocked & locked" in 1911 fashion, or uncocked as a double action. This gun is outfitted with a 6" stainless steel National Match Grade barrel, that mitigates muzzle rise down to next to nothing. It has a HK competition recoil spring, making the racking of the slide feel like hot butter on teflon. It is easier to rack than EVERY 9mm I own. One of the most significant features of the USP is the mechanical recoil reduction system. One of the most significant features of the USP is the mechanical recoil reduction system. This system is incorporated into the recoil spring assembly, and consists of a captive coil spring around the guide rod. These two features in concert, make this gun feel more like a 40 S&W, even with 45 +P loads. It has the HK short reset combat trigger, that allows for a higher cyclic rate, without being dangerously light like a competition trigger. Included with the gun are 3) 12 round factory, and 1) 22 round aftermarket magazines, a black leather pancake style belt holster. She has HK installed night sights, that are dimming, but still work like a charm. The frame rails, exterior of the chamber and feed ramps have all been polished to a mirror shine. This was my personal sidearm on a security detail in N. Africa, and she served me well, not once giving me a click when I wanted a bang (regardless of ammo), and supremely accurate and manageable. She has some minor scratches on the proprietary "Hostile Environment" nitride finish, but nothing down to the bare metal. Overall, I'd put the finish in the 80-85% category. The bore is bright and shiney, with great rifling, and the gun functions flawlessly. This isn't a civilian toy, but rather a professional's tool.
